Ad Text:
About Us

Sigma Healthcare is proudly powering pharmacy! We have the largest pharmacy network in Australia with trusted brands including Chemist Warehouse, Amcal and Discount Drug Stores. We are powered by our dedicated people and our leading Australian full-line pharmacy wholesale and distribution business that delivers medicines to any pharmacy anywhere in Australia. With Chemist Warehouse now operating in four countries outside Australia, we continue to expand our reach.


The Opportunity

We’re looking for a commercially minded Financial Analyst to support our Wholesale Commercial team with high-quality reporting, analysis, and insights that drive stronger financial performance.

Reporting to the Commercial Finance Manager – Wholesale, you’ll partner closely with Commercial leaders to interpret financial results, support margin improvement initiatives, and enhance decision-making across one of the most critical areas of the business.

This role is ideal for an analytical, detail-driven finance professional who enjoys problem-solving, business partnering, and taking ownership of key financial processes in a fast-moving and transforming ASX-listed environment.




Key Responsibilities

Partner with the Wholesale Commercial team to interpret monthly financial results

Own the month-end close process for Commercial cost centres

Support development and continuous improvement of the CPM model

Analyse business performance to provide insight on sales, margins, volume, mix, price and COGS

Prepare accurate and timely monthly financial performance reporting for Commercial Leaders, Executives and the Board

Review and analyse financial and non-financial data to identify trends, risks and opportunities

Support annual budgets and rolling monthly forecasts

Champion continuous improvement across finance systems and reporting

Build strong engagement and customer-focused relationships with key stakeholders




About You
To succeed in this role, you’ll bring:

CA or CPA qualification (or near completion)

Strong financial and commercial acumen

Advanced Excel skills

Experience in finance business partnering, ideally within FMCG, wholesale or retail

Proven ability to analyse complex datasets and deliver actionable insights

Strong communication and stakeholder management capability

A proactive, curious mindset with a continuous-improvement focus




Why Join Us?
At Sigma Healthcare, our people make the difference. Here’s what you can expect:

Competitive salary + superannuation

Hybrid working arrangements (Preston HQ)

Staff discounts across all Sigma Healthcare group stores (Chemist Warehouse, Ultra Beauty, My Beauty Spot, Discount Drug Store & Optometrist Warehouse

Exposure to senior commercial stakeholders

Career progression in a Top 50 ASX-listed company

A collaborative, high-performing Commercial Finance team




Apply Now
If you’re ready to shape financial insights and support commercial decision-making across Australia’s largest pharmacy network, apply now and help power the future of pharmacy with Sigma Healthcare.

About Us

We are an award-winning Oracle consultancy, providing Project Management, Technology and Training services to support capital-intensive projects. We work collaboratively with clients to provide outstanding value every time.

 At Prescience Technology, our team is a group of passionate experts who love solving complex problems, exploring emerging technologies, and helping our clients run their projects smarter. Our Cloud & Managed Services team sits at the heart of what we do — delivering exceptional service, building real relationships, and keeping our clients’ systems running at their best.

The Opportunity

As a Senior Consultant, you’ll be the go-to technical expert for our Oracle Primavera and Project Controls clients. You’ll lead with confidence, think on your feet, and make a real impact by keeping projects running smoothly and clients feeling supported.

You’ll balance hands-on delivery with strategic thinking like improving processes, guiding clients, and helping shape how we deliver managed services across the business.

What You’ll Be Doing

Deliver great service, every time – Shape the delivery of Cloud & Managed Services (Primavera Suite & related apps) in line with client SLAs.

Be the expert – Provide technical guidance on Oracle Primavera, databases, and cloud platforms like Oracle Cloud, AWS, and Azure.

Keep projects on track – Work closely with project managers to deliver outcomes on time and within scope.

Find better ways – Identify and drive process improvements that make a real difference to how we work and how clients experience our services.

Build strong connections – Work closely with internal teams and clients. Communicate clearly, stay proactive, and always aim for excellence.

Stay sharp – Keep learning and adapting to emerging technologies to stay ahead of the curve.

What You’ll Bring

Proven experience in Managed Services or Project Controls environments.

Solid technical knowledge across Oracle Primavera, databases (Oracle/SQL), and cloud platforms (Oracle Cloud, AWS, Azure).

A knack for problem-solving and improving how things are done.

Great communication and stakeholder skills — you know how to build trust and make complex things simple.

Strong organisational skills — you can manage priorities, meet deadlines, and keep projects moving.

Tertiary qualifications in IT, Engineering, or a related field.

Certifications like PMP, PRINCE2, or Cloud/Database credentials are a big tick.

 Why You’ll Love Working Here

A culture that values curiosity, collaboration, and continuous learning.

The freedom to explore new tech and challenge the status quo.

Opportunities to grow your career and make your mark.

A supportive team that celebrates wins — big and small.

Flexibility to work your way – hybrid and remote options available


If this sounds like your kind of opportunity, we would love to hear from you.

Company description:



About Us

The Department of Transport and Planning oversees key planning, transport and land use policy decisions and management across the State. A life-cycle approach to planning, building, connecting and sustaining communities means our people can come together to; improve services, deliver sustainable projects, focus on customer engagement, streamline regulatory approval pathways, facilitate community consultation and better realise local economic opportunities for more liveable communities across Victoria.

Network Design and Integration delivers transport priorities through the planning, development and maintenance of an integrated pipeline of projects and strategic initiatives that provide safe, efficient and sustainable outcomes to all Victorians.

We're focused on outcomes that deliver more choice, connections and confidence in our travel, ensuring the whole transport network works as one to deliver better services and outcomes.



Job description:



About the Role

The Manager, Asset Data Reporting and Visualisation is a position that sits within the Asset Information Requirements, Governance and Reporting Team in Asset Intelligence Branch of Assets and Engineering Division. The position leads the on-going management of asset related data reporting and visualisation capabilities that align with business needs, organisational objectives and regulatory requirements.

This position ensures that timely and accurate asset reports and dashboards are available to meet DTP reporting and visualisation decision-making including strategic asset management, asset assurance, monitoring of asset health, lifecycle performance, risks and other asset management activities across the asset lifecycle.

The position plays a critical role in bridging technical data outputs with business needs by collaborating closely with stakeholders across asset management to ensure reporting outputs are aligned with organisational goals and priorities.

To access the Position Description, please click here.

Position Outcomes / Accountabilities

Asset Data Reporting and Visualisation - The incumbent leads the development, implementation and continuous improvement of asset data reporting and visualisation capabilities that align with organisational objectives and business needs.
Asset Reports and Dashboards Development - The incumbent provides advanced expertise and knowledge in the production, management and improvement of dashboards and reports using tools such as Power BI, Tableau or similar platform to provide clear, targeted and timely reports that contributes to regulatory submissions, audits, and reporting obligations related to asset inventory, condition and performance.
Asset Data Mining and Integration - The incumbent develops methods to obtain/access data from asset custodians and stewards, asset information specialists, and collaborate with data engineers and modellers to ensure data from multiple sources (e.g. Enterprise Asset Management System, GIS, Analytics Platform, SCADA) are harmonised and integrated for reporting.
Asset Trend Analysis - The incumbent applies sound statistical and analytical techniques to build and maintain methodologies to enable trend analysis in asset condition, performance, failure rates to support evidence-based problem solving with respect to asset management lifecycle activities.
Stakeholder Management - The incumbent demonstrates excellent interpersonal and communication skills, with the ability to collaborate with a range of internal and external stakeholders to understand business needs and requirements to ensure delivery of value-added reporting solutions.
In line with Section 31A of the Public Administration Act 2004 (Vic) other duties may be assigned consistent with employment classification, skills, and capabilities.

Key Selection Criteria

The DTP is seeking a professional with strong data literacy and reporting expertise to analyse complex datasets, generate meaningful insights, and support effective decision-making. You will apply accomplished critical thinking, stakeholder management, and organisational asset management capabilities to deliver value-add outcomes and drive service improvements. The role also encourages innovation and continuous improvement, contributing ideas and enhancing processes to improve quality and efficiency.

Qualifications and Experience

Mandatory

Tertiary qualifications in data analytics, data science, statistics, asset management and/or engineering related disciplines
Experience in data visualisation development through BI Tools such as Power BI, Tableau
Experience in people management and team leadership
Experience in complex infrastructure, asset and/or engineering data management

Desirable

Experience in one or more programming languages (R, SQL, Python)
Experience in Asset Management, preferably in Transport industry (Roads, Rail, Bus)
Experience in managing geospatial data (Shapefile, GeoJSON, WKT, KML, KMZ) and products (Esri)

Culture Value

We welcome applicants from a diverse range of backgrounds representing the community that we serve, including veterans, parents, carers, First Peoples, people with disability, multicultural, multifaith and LGBTIQA+ individuals.

As an equal opportunity employer, we are committed to fostering a safe, inclusive, and high-performance culture. Through shared actions and behaviours aligned with our strategy and direction, we empower our people to thrive and meaningfully contribute to the department's goals.

What we offer

Meaningful work making Victorian communities more accessible and liveable
Professional growth and development opportunities across the department and the wider Victorian Public Services
A hybrid working model focused on collaboration and teamwork
Optimal work-life balance initiatives including flexible working arrangements
Opportunity to work across multiple urban and suburban hubs
We prioritise the development of a safe and inclusive culture

Pre-employment checks and employment conditions

All new appointments to the department will be subject to a National Criminal Records Check, Misconduct Screening, and a Qualification Check where there is a requirement for a mandatory qualification. Information provided to the Department of Transport and Planning will be treated in the strictest confidence consistent with the requirements of the Privacy and Data Protection Act 2014.

Applicants must be an Australian Citizen, Permanent Resident or hold a valid work permit or visa necessary for the nature of the position.

Recipients of Victorian Public Service (VPS) voluntary departure packages should note that re-employment restrictions apply.

Non-VPS applicants will be subject to a probation period of six months.

How to Apply

Click the ‘Apply' button to be redirected to our recruitment platform, where you may need to create an account to submit your application.

If you encounter any issues, refer to our Quick Reference Guide for step-by-step instructions.

Applications close at 11:59 pm on Tuesday 02 December 2025.

Please include both your resume and a cover letter. All applications must be submitted via the online portal, we're unable to accept email or manual submissions.

For further information about the role, please contact Cassie Khaw, Senior Manager Asset Information Requirements, Governance and Reporting via cassie.khaw@transport.vic.gov.au

Important Information:

If you require any adjustments to fully participate in the recruitment process, or need the advert or attachments in an accessible format (e.g., large print), please contact us by phone or email. We're here to support you.

Our client is one of the largest companies in Australia and is continuing to grow as they acquire new customers and expand their footprint across the country. 2025 was another record for the business and the company is on target to achieve $1 billion in revenues by 2028.

As Financial Planning and Analysis Manager, you will be in charge of leading the financial planning, budgeting and forecasting processes to support strategic decision-making and drive performance and growth. Key responsibilities include overseeing budgets, performing financial analysis, creating financial models and forecasts, monitoring performance and providing actionable insights to the Executive Management Team.

This is a manager role with the Finance team with high exposure to the CFO and EMT.

The role requires strong analytical skills, technical proficiency in financial software and effective collaboration with various business stakeholders. 

Ideally, you will have at least 5-10 years in a senior FP+A role from a large organisation.

In addition, we are looking for:-
· CPA or CA qualification
· Bachelor degree in Accounting, Finance, Commerce, Economics or equivalent required
· Masters degree in Accounting, Finance or Business Administration preferred
· Excellent coordination, planning and organisational skills
 
In return, you can expect to significantly accelerate your career and and enjoy the mentorship of a top ranking CFO.

$150,000 plus super plus bonus.

Support Data and Analytics Engineer - 6 month Contract 

Flexible work from home arrangements

Location: North Sydney, 2060




ABOUT EG

Ideas are becoming a reality across the EG Australia national network as we deliver a consistent retail strategy in specialist forecourt retailing to our customers. We continue to build and grow, supported by the knowledge and success of EG Group a creative and innovative global retail operation servicing over 6,500 forecourts in 9 countries across Europe, North America and Australia.




ABOUT THE ROLE

As a Support Data & Analytics Engineer, you’ll provide essential reporting and data support for 500+ stores and key business units, including Finance, Operations, Fuel Pricing, Merchandising, Business Assurance, and People & Culture. You’ll manage and resolve ServiceNow support tickets by identifying root causes, re-running pipelines, validating data quality, and working with upstream system owners to fix data or logic issues.

You’ll also perform analytical investigations to detect issues, anomalies, and trends, collaborating closely with the wider EG Australia Support Team to ensure accurate and reliable information management.




RESPONSIBILITIES IN A SNAPSHOT:

Reporting into the Head of Information Management you will:

Monitor and action support tickets daily in the ServiceNow queue, along with investigating the underlying trends and anomalies

Liaise with internal users and escalate more complex issues to senior engineers or development teams

Processing ensuring all data processing is completed in a timely manner to ensure downstream reporting and analytics are up to date

Design, test and implement effective and scalable data pipelines, leveraging cutting-edge tools such as LucidCharts (to design), SQL (to build) and Azure Data Factory (to schedule)

Design, test and implement effective and scalable data pipelines in Azure Data Factor

Enhance and maintain data storage and processing solutions, across data warehouses and data lakes using Azure.

Automate data analysis and reporting processes, utilising various tools and scripts

Support data governance through implementing best practices around code documentation, naming conventions, data glossaries and data mapping

Partner with stakeholders to translate complex business problems into fit-for-purpose and scalable data pipelines and data models, to enable fast and efficient data-driven decision-making




WHAT ARE WE LOOKING FOR?

A Bachelor’s degree in Data Engineering, Computer Science, or a related field

4 years of experience in a data engineering or analytics role, with a strong foundation in working with complex data systems

Strong problem-solving and analytical skills, with a natural curiosity for digging into data and identifying solutions

Excellent communication and presentation skills, with the ability to engage and manage stakeholders effectively

A proactive and collaborative approach, you work well independently and as part of a team

Proficiency in Snowflake and advanced SQL scripting, along with intermediate skills in a programming language such as Python

Hands-on experience with ETL and scheduling tools like Azure Data Factory, Azure Logic Apps, PowerAutomate, or similar platforms

A solid understanding of data modelling principles, practices, and methodologies

Experience creating and maintaining technical documentation, standards, and best-practice guidance

Demonstrated expertise in database design, Master Data Management (MDM), and building high-performance, scalable data pipelines




WHAT’S IN IT FOR YOU?

An opportunity to play an integral role in driving efficiency and profitability for EG Australia.

Competitive salary package and employee discounts.

Mix of office & working from home flexibility with access to employee well-being programs.

Work with cutting edge analytics & AI tools across Azure, Snowflake and DataIKU.

Equal opportunity workplace with a commitment to diversity & inclusion and gender-diverse policies.

 

Be part of the team shaping operations for EG Australia. Apply Now

Company description:



About us
We create thriving places and connected communities. We bring together transport, planning, land use, precinct and policy functions in a single department to deliver the best outcomes for Victorians.


Together with our portfolio agencies, we are responsible for planning, building, operating and +maintaining Victoria's transport, planning and land services for use by all.


We foster a safe, inclusive and constructive place to work.


Integrated Strategy is a Division within the Office of the Secretary, which provides oversight to policy change and operates as a policy coordination and strategy function within DTP. Integrated Strategy works with external stakeholders and across the Department to co-design policies and strategies to respond to current and future challenges.



Job description:



About the role
This role is in a newly created Strategy Branch in the Integrated Strategy Division of the Department. The purpose of the Branch is to lead longer term strategy work for the Department. Reporting to the Director, the Principal Strategy Advisor will be part of a small team that together with other members of the Integrated Strategy Division will work with leaders from across DTP on high priority strategy topics identified by DTP leadership.


The Principal Strategy Advisor will take a leading role on strategic workstreams through facilitating workshops, designing and executing cross departmental engagement approaches, structuring complex problems and fully owning the delivery of work against them spanning work planning, analysis, synthesising and end product creation.

Key Selection Criteria
The role requires demonstrated leadership in critical thinking, problem solving and project delivery, with the ability to analyse complex issues in a broader organisational context, develop effective solutions and translate strategic direction into successful programs and initiatives. Strong data literacy is essential, including the ability to design data collection and analysis approaches that support informed, predictive decision-making. The position also demands a future-focused mindset, highly effective communication skills and the ability to build a collaborative culture across internal and external stakeholders.

To access the Position Description, please click here.

Position accountabilities
The Department of Transport and Planning is seeking an experienced and influential Principal Strategy Advisor to play a key role in shaping strategic direction across Victoria's transport system. This senior position is responsible for guiding major strategic work, leading complex analysis and ensuring the department's priorities are clearly defined, well-evidenced and aligned with broader organisational goals.


In this role, you will work closely with senior leaders to distil diverse inputs into clear strategic focus areas. You will scope, research and complete complex qualitative and quantitative analysis to inform high-quality written strategy products that support long-term decision-making. Your ability to synthesise information, think critically across multiple time horizons and translate insights into impactful strategy documents will be central to your success.


The role also involves managing projects that underpin the development and implementation of key strategic products. You will coordinate timelines, monitor progress, identify risks and proactively provide solutions, ensuring the Strategy Director is kept informed of critical milestones and challenges. Your leadership will help embed strategic outcomes across the department, ensuring they translate into real and enduring impact.


This is an opportunity to influence State-wide strategic priorities and contribute to shaping the future of transport and planning in Victoria. If you are a strategic thinker with strong analytical capability, excellent stakeholder skills and a commitment to delivering high-quality work, we encourage you to apply.


Qualifications and experience
Mandatory
- Tertiary qualification or extensive experience in an analytical or technical field. (mandatory)
- Experience working with complex and disparate data sets to draw strategic insights (mandatory)
- Exposure to problem structuring and analytical approaches (mandatory)

Desirable
- Knowledge and experience in Transport and/or Planning (desirable)

Culture Value
We welcome applicants from a diverse range of backgrounds representing the community that we serve, including veterans, parents, carers, First Peoples, people with disability, multicultural, multifaith and LGBTIQA+ individuals.


As an equal opportunity employer, we are committed to fostering a safe, inclusive, and high-performance culture. Through shared actions and behaviours aligned with our strategy and direction, we empower our people to thrive and meaningfully contribute to the department's goals.


What we offer
Working at the Department of Transport and Planning provides people with the opportunity to contribute to creating thriving places and connected communities for all Victorians.


For further details please refer to Careers at the Department of Transport and Planning.


Pre-employment checks and employment conditions
All new appointments to the department will be subject to a National Criminal Records Check, Misconduct Screening, and a Qualification Check where there is a requirement for a mandatory qualification. Information provided to the Department of Transport and Planning will be treated in the strictest confidence consistent with the requirements of the Privacy and Data Protection Act 2014.


Applicants must be an Australian Citizen, Permanent Resident or hold a valid work permit or visa necessary for the nature of the position.


Recipients of Victorian Public Service (VPS) voluntary departure packages should note that re-employment restrictions apply.

Non-VPS applicants will be subject to a probation period of six months.


How to apply
Click the ‘Apply' button to be redirected to our recruitment platform, where you may need to create an account to submit your application.

If you encounter any issues, refer to our Quick Reference Guide for step-by-step instructions.


Applications close at 11.59pm on Tuesday, 2nd December 2025.

Please include both your resume and a cover letter. All applications must be submitted via the online portal, we're unable to accept email or manual submissions.

For further information about the role, please contact Jules Flynn - Executive Director, Integrated Strategy via jules.flynn@transport.vic.gov.au.

IXOM plays a vital part in the lives of tens of millions of people every day. We're the experts behind the scenes, ensuring safe and reliable access and helping industries, businesses, and local communities thrive.


Our products, services and solutions are used across many end markets, including dairy, agriculture, viticulture, electricity, steel, food and beverage, pulp and paper, mining and construction, and water treatment (just to name a few).


We are supported by over 1,300 people globally and our operations span across four continents and nine countries, with headquarters in Melbourne, Australia.





About your role

Reporting to the Head of Business Process Data & Analytics within the Technology & Transformation (T&T) team, the Business Process Analyst will be instrumental in driving meaningful change across IXOM's internal operations. This role is all about uncovering opportunities—identifying and validating process challenges, facilitating stakeholder workshops, and conducting current state assessments to pave the way for smarter, more efficient ways of working.

If you're passionate about process excellence, thrive in collaborative environments, and love turning complexity into clarity, this is your chance to make a lasting impact.

Key Responsibilities

Drive Process Optimisation: Analyse existing processes to identify opportunities for simplification, standardisation, and automation.
Lead Continuous Improvement: Initiate and support process improvement initiatives that enhance efficiency and support strategic goals.
Engage Stakeholders: Facilitate workshops and act as a key liaison between business units, the Technology & Transformation team, and Organisational Change Management.
Document and Communicate Clearly: Develop and maintain comprehensive process documentation, SOPs, and training materials to support change adoption.
Support Project Delivery: Align process work with project timelines and objectives, providing business analysis support and ensuring timely execution.

Who are we looking for?

Bachelor's degree in business Analytics, Business Process Management, Business Management or a related field.
Relevant business process improvement related qualifications including Six Sigma or similar
Proven experience as a Business Analyst or a suitable management role, with a focus on business improvement and optimisation.
Analytical Thinking: Ability to analyse complex processes and identify areas for improvement.
Communication: Strong verbal and written communication skills to effectively interact with stakeholders at all levels.
Attention to Detail: Meticulous attention to detail in process documentation and analysis.
Adaptability: Ability to adapt to changing business needs and priorities.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with a keen understanding of business processes.
Familiarity with process mapping.
Familiarity with process mapping standards and tools/technologies (e.g. Signavio) an advantage
Ability to work collaboratively in a team-oriented environment.
Experience participating in projects and supporting deliverables, timelines, and teams.
Understanding of automation and standardisation principles in business processes.

Benefits at IXOM


For a start, you'll work for a large global organisation, where you'll not only earn a competitive salary, but you'll also have access to an Employee Assistance Program, a recognition program, and a range of health and wellness benefits and discounts.

Our wellbeing program is second to none, and we offer a range of education assistance and learning resources, as well as secondment and promotion opportunities to help you grow both personally and professionally.

We support what's important to you by promoting workplace giving, diversity and providing volunteering leave, and, of course, we offer flexible working wherever possible.

To Apply

If this sounds like you, we'd love to hear from you!

Our Process

At IXOM we are committed to employing individuals who align with our values and meet the requirements of the role. As part of the recruitment process, there are a number of checks which may be conducted to demonstrate applicants' suitability for a role including police / criminal background checks, medical, drug and alcohol testing, and reference checks.

Diverse candidates have diverse needs. During your recruitment journey, information will be provided about adjustment requests. If you require additional support before submitting your application, please contact our Talent Acquisition team.

Careers with Impact

More than one million Australians trust HESTA with their money. HESTA is a top-performing industry super fund working for real-world impact. We use our expertise and influence to deliver strong long-term returns while accelerating our contribution to a more sustainable world.

HESTA is also an inspiring and rewarding place to work. That's because what we do makes a difference to the lives of our members. The people who work at HESTA are not only exceptional at what they do, they're focused on living and creating a strong organisational culture. We're an industry super fund dedicated to the people who keep our communities going. People who provide some of the best health, education and community services in the world are HESTA members - and we are proud to serve them.





Bring your authentic and passionate self to this exceptional role #careerswithimpact

Please note this role could be based in Sydney or Melbourne.


As the Senior Investment Analyst - Fixed Income, you will support the Defensive Assets team in the implementation and oversight of HESTA's internal Fixed Income, Cash and Enhanced Cash portfolio management activities.

Reporting to the Portfolio Manager - Fixed Income, you will be involved in portfolio management support, including portfolio construction, risk management, and trade idea generation based on quantitative analysis. Leading quantitative research initiatives, you will develop and refine investment processes while identifying new portfolio construction opportunities through data-driven analysis.

Your role will encompass risk management and compliance responsibilities, ensuring adherence to investment mandates and contributing to our risk management framework. You will design and implement quantitative models for interest rate and credit analysis, while creating and maintaining portfolio optimization tools.

About You

Essential for this role is experience in fixed income portfolio management combined with skills and experience in Debt Capital Markets and in the practical application of quantitative methodologies and techniques to Fixed Income Portfolio Management and Trade Execution.

The ideal candidate will possess qualifications in Finance, Actuarial Studies, Econometrics or related fields, along with intermediate to advanced skills in Python and/or R. Required experience includes financial modelling, yield curve analysis, portfolio construction, derivatives trading, relative value analysis and risk management in a Portfolio Management or Dealing Room environment. You will have well developed sector knowledge of defensive asset classes (credit, debt, cash) and FX and experience in portfolio construction and risk management.

Benefits that matter and make a difference for our employees


o Leave for those moments that matter, an additional 6 days of leave at the end of year, up to 6 days paid volunteer leave, gender neutral paid parental leave of 20 weeks, Gender Affirmation leave, reproductive health and wellbeing leave, Cultural and Ceremonial leave. Access your LSL after 3 years, take AL at half pay, and purchase up to 2 weeks additional leave (just to name a few!).
o Your Professional development matters, up to $5k per year professional development and up to 8 days professional development leave, HESTA scholarships and free access to a range of premium learning tools.
o Your health and wellbeing matters, free annual flu shots and skin checks, incredible social events throughout the year and a comprehensive employee assistance program available 24/7.
o Your financial wellbeing matters, 15% super, financial planning support, end of year payment for all Enterprise Agreement-covered employees, incentivised Employee Referral Program and novated lease options.

We celebrate, value and include people of all backgrounds, genders, identities, cultures and abilities. We welcome and support applications from First Nations people, physically, neuro or culturally diverse, LGBTQI+, and people of any age. We are proud to be WGEA accredited as an Employer of Choice for Gender Equity.


We want all candidates to feel safe, included and provided with the best opportunity to thrive, if you require reasonable adjustments during your application or throughout the recruitment process, please reach out to a member of the Talent team careers@hesta.com.au and we'll call you to discuss.

New opportunity to work across Internally Managed Fixed Income, Credit and Cash portfolios at a major super fund





Flexible Hybrid Working

Enhanced Leave Entitlements

Process Analyst 
 
Project Overview:
Our client in the leisure space is transitioning from its legacy on-premise Opera PMS (v5.6) to Oracle's Opera Cloud platform across 10 Club and Resort properties, including Opera Sales & Catering (S&C) for Conference & Events. This migration will modernize operations, reduce on-premise infrastructure, and enable industry-standard features.

Role Details

Location: Melbourne, Victoria
Contract: 6-Month Contingent
Work Model: Hybrid (3 days in-office)
Key Responsibilities

Analyse and document current-state business processes and define future-state workflows aligned with Opera Cloud capabilities.
Collaborate with delivery teams to ensure process changes are implemented effectively during system configuration and migration.
Conduct impact assessments for process changes across hospitality operations and Conference & Events.
Support testing activities by validating process alignment during SIT and UAT phases.
Facilitate workshops with stakeholders to confirm process requirements and resolve gaps.
Develop process documentation, SOPs, and training materials to support operational readiness.
Identify risks and dependencies related to process changes and escalate as needed.
Skills & Experience

Strong background in business process analysis and modelling (BPMN or similar).
Experience in hospitality or leisure industry systems, ideally PMS platforms.
Ability to manage stakeholder engagement and drive consensus on process changes.
Familiarity with cloud migration projects and integration considerations.
Proficiency with Jira, Confluence, and process modelling tools (Visio, draw.io).
Agile delivery experience and ability to work in fast-paced environments.

LTI Mindtree is seeking an experienced Azure Analytics Data Architect to lead the design and delivery of enterprise-grade Azure data platforms for public sector and large enterprise clients. This role requires strong expertise across Azure analytics services, data engineering best practices, and cloud architectural governance. The ideal candidate will bring deep technical capability, architectural leadership, and the ability to design secure, scalable, and future-ready data ecosystems. Active NV1/NV2 security clearance is mandatory.

Key Responsibilities

Architect and implement end-to-end Azure data solutions spanning ingestion, storage, processing, analytics, and governance.
Define and maintain enterprise-wide Azure data architecture standards that align with security, compliance, and operational frameworks.
Utilize key Azure services such as Microsoft Fabric, Databricks, Synapse Analytics, Data Lake Storage, Data Factory, Cosmos DB, and Azure SQL to deliver high-performing solutions.
Build, optimize, and automate scalable ETL/ELT pipelines using ADF, Synapse, metadata-driven frameworks, and CI/CD practices.
Provide architectural leadership across data modeling, integration workflows, analytics pipelines, and cross-system interoperability.
Implement strong data governance, data quality, identity controls, and privacy protection across Azure environments.
Collaborate with data scientists, analysts, and application teams to deliver structured, governed, and accessible datasets.
Create and maintain architecture documentation, solution blueprints, and implementation roadmaps.
Ensure architecture alignment with Microsoft Cloud Adoption Framework (CAF), Well-Architected Framework (WAF), and organizational technology standards.
Drive continuous improvement across performance, reliability, cost optimization, operational excellence, and security posture.
Qualifications

Active NV1/NV2 Security Clearance (mandatory, role cannot be performed without it)
10+ years of experience in Data Architecture, Data Engineering, Cloud Analytics, or enterprise data platform delivery
Deep hands-on expertise with Azure analytics services including Data Factory, Synapse, Databricks, Data Lake, Fabric, Cosmos DB, and Azure SQL
Strong knowledge of data modeling, warehousing concepts, ETL/ELT best practices, and distributed data processing
Experience working with both relational and NoSQL data systems, including PostgreSQL and Cosmos DB
Proven capability in designing scalable, secure, and governed cloud architectures at enterprise scale
Experience with CI/CD, infrastructure-as-code, metadata-driven frameworks, and modern DevOps practices
Exceptional communication, documentation, and stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to convey complex architecture concepts to both technical and business audiences

At LTI Mindtree Australia, you’ll have the opportunity to work on nation-critical transformation programs while being part of a global organization known for innovation, excellence, and a strong Azure data practice. You will join a collaborative team that values technical leadership, continuous learning, and impactful delivery. This is your chance to shape the data landscape for some of the region’s most strategic clients, all while growing your career in a supportive and future-focused environment.

Category: Policy, Planning & Regulation, Government - State (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
Your new opportunity:
As a Principal Treasury Analyst, you will lead the monitoring and analysis of financial and non-financial performance across Queensland Government agencies, providing strategic advice to support the development and implementation of sound public policy.

This is an exciting opportunity to work with internal and external clients and stakeholders to address complex financial and policy matters, identify risks, and develop strategic solutions that align with the Government's economic priorities. You will play a critical role in delivering high-quality advice, reports and recommendations to senior executives, ministerial offices and interdepartmental committees, ensuring that Queensland Treasury continues to drive the state's economic growth and sustainability.

In this role, you will:
• Provide strategic advice and support to clients and senior executives on complex budget, financial management, and policy issues.
• Lead the development and implementation of processes to monitor and analyse agencies' budget and financial information.
• Offer expert advice on risk identification, management, and evaluation of best practice financial strategies and policies.
• Manage relationships with clients and stakeholders to resolve complex issues and negotiate positive outcomes.
• Represent Treasury on internal and external committees and interdepartmental working groups.
• Prepare complex reports, submissions, briefing notes, and correspondence within tight timeframes.
• Support organisational strategy, direction, and initiatives.

What experience you will bring:
To excel in this role, you will demonstrate:
• The ability to lead teams and deliver outcomes in a complex and time-sensitive environment.
• Experience in analysing financial and non-financial performance data and/or developing government policy.
• Expertise in providing strategic, practical, and solutions-focused analysis and advice.
• Influential communication skills tailored to diverse audiences.
• Strong interpersonal and relationship management skills to foster collaboration and information sharing.
• Effective judgement and understanding of different perspectives to develop solutions and work collaboratively.

Whilst there are no mandatory qualifications needed for this role, relevant qualifications will be highly regarded.

How to apply:
To submit your application, click on the Apply link to provide:
• Your resume detailing relevant experience.
• A cover letter of no more than two pages outlining why you are interested in this position and how your knowledge, skills and experience makes you a strong candidate for the role.
